Optional: did you consider to have a setup() and tearDown() to initialize and rollback the env variable?
Since seems important to restore the env var at the end of the test I prefer to have it in a method to avoid any problem if in the future we'll refactor this test and accidentally remove the finally clause.
Good point. I'll try to rewrite it.
jest.clearAllMocks()   can be used instead of all
Oh, you are right. I'll fix it.
const zoweApi can reused to get out the duplication, via initializing it in beforeEach
